> Since we like to keep things pretty PG13 around these parts, we won't get into the specifics of why pomegranate is considered to be an aphrodisiac. Suffice to say that once you've popped a few of these passion pills in your pilaff, things could take a seriously fun turn on the 14th. Turn up that Marvin Gaye album and let's get it on.

Chop the @onion{1} in half lengthways through the root then peel off the skin. Place the onion halves flat on the #chopping board{}, then slice them very, very thinly widthways into half moons. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}. Peel the skin from the @ginger{1}(peeled and finely chopped) using the edge of a #spoon{} then very finely chop.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #saucepan{} on medium-low heat. Add in the onion, garlic and ginger and gently cook for ~{6%mins} until soft. Do not let the mixture brown off. If it's cooking too fast, add @water{1%tbsp} and turn the heat lower.

Stir the @curry powder mix{1} (not the garam masala) into the mixture together with @water{350%ml}. Bring the mixture to a bubble and dissolve in half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Add the @basmati rice{1} and @garam masala{1}, turn the heat to its lowest setting and put a #lid{} on the pan. Leave for ~{10%mins} on the heat, then ~{10%mins} off the heat. Don't peek under the lid until 20 mins are up or the rice won't cook properly.

After that, gently rub the garam masala together with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} into each @tilapia fillet{2}. When the rice is almost finished, heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium high heat.

Once the oil is nice and hot (it'll shimmer and move around the pan more like water) gently place the fillets into the pan away from your body (to stop getting splattered). Cook the fish for ~{4%mins} on the skin side without touching them, then gently flip them over and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Finely chop @mint{3%tbsp} and stir this through the rice, then serve the fish on top with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2} and the @pomegranate seeds{1}.

> Do not let the mixture brown off when cooking the onion, garlic and ginger - if it's cooking too fast, add water to slow it down.

> Don't peek under the lid until 20 minutes are up or the rice won't cook properly.